" href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/IsSubnormal.html#AddSubgroup.IsSubnormal.top\"><span class=\"name\">AddSubgroup</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsSubnormal</span>.<span class=\"name\">top</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">G</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#AddGroup\">AddGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Notation.html#Top.top\">⊤</a>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/IsSubnormal.html#AddSubgroup.IsSubnormal\">IsSubnormal</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The whole additive subgroup `G` is subnormal in itself. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/IsSubnormal.html#AddSubgroup.IsSubnormal.top","kind":"ctor","line":84,"name":"AddSubgroup.IsSubnormal.top","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/GroupTheory/IsSubnormal.lean#L84-L85"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">inductive</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/IsSubnormal.html#AddSubgroup.IsSubnormal\"><span class=\"name\">AddSubgroup</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsSubnormal</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">G</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#AddGroup\">AddGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Subgroup/Defs.html#AddSubgroup\">AddSubgroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"An additive subgroup `H` of an additive group `G` satisfies `IsSubnormal` if\n* either `H = ⊤`;\n* or there is an additive subgroup `K` of `G` containing `H` and such that `H` is normal in `K` and\n  `K` satisfies `IsSubnormal`.\n\nEquivalently, `H.IsSubnormal` means that there is a chain of additive subgroups\n`H₀ ≤ H₁ ≤ ... ≤ Hₙ` such that\n* `H = H₀`,\n* `G = Hₙ`,\n* for each `i ∈ {0, ..., n - 1}`, `Hᵢ` is a normal additive subgroup of `Hᵢ₊₁`.\n\nSee `isSubnormal_iff` for this characterisation.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/IsSubnormal.html#AddSubgroup.IsSubnormal","kind":"inductive","line":70,"name":"AddSubgroup.IsSubnormal","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/GroupTheory/IsSubnormal.lean#L70-L89"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/IsSubnormal.html#Subgroup.IsSubnormal.step\"><span class=\"name\">Subgroup</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsSubnormal</span>.<span class=\"name\">step</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">G</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#Group\">Group</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">H </span><span class=\"fn\">K</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Subgroup/Defs.html#Subgroup\">Subgroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h_le</span> : <span class=\"fn\">H</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hSubn</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">K</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/IsSubnormal.html#Subgroup.IsSubnormal\">IsSubnormal</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hN</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">H</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Subgroup/Map.html#Subgroup.subgroupOf\">subgroupOf</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">K</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Subgroup/Defs.html#Subgroup.Normal\">Normal</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">H</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/IsSubnormal.html#Subgroup.IsSubnormal\">IsSubnormal</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A subgroup `H` is subnormal if there is a subnormal subgroup `K` containing `H` that is\nsubnormal itself and such that `H` is normal in `K`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/IsSubnormal.html#Subgroup.IsSubnormal.step","kind":"ctor","line":65,"name":"Subgroup.IsSubnormal.step","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/GroupTheory/IsSubnormal.lean#L65-L68"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/IsSubnormal.html#Subgroup.IsSubnormal.top\"><span class=\"name\">Subgroup</span>.<span class=\"name\">IsSubnormal</span>.<span class=\"name\">top</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">G</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"i