means that there is a chain of subgroups\n`H₀ ≤ H₁ ≤ ... ≤ Hₙ` such that\n* `H = H₀`,\n* `G = Hₙ`,\n* for each `i ∈ {0, ..., n - 1}`, `Hᵢ` is a normal subgroup of `Hᵢ₊₁`.\n\nSee `isSubnormal_iff` for this characterisation.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/IsSubnormal.html#Subgroup.IsSubnormal","kind":"inductive","line":49,"name":"Subgroup.IsSubnormal","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/GroupTheory/IsSubnormal.lean#L49-L68"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.GroupTheory.Subgroup.Simple"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.GroupTheory.IsSubnormal"}